<emphasis id="B91AEAB5FF7CFF17D4CCF83F0C1AF83D" bold="true" box="[199,322,1940,1966]" pageId="129" pageNumber="130">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Males of 
<taxonomicName id="4C6E4D24FF7CFF17D5B7F83F0E37F83D" authority="Jocque &amp; Baert, 2002" authorityName="Jocque &amp; Baert" authorityYear="2002" box="[444,879,1940,1967]" class="Arachnida" family="Zodariidae" genus="Tenedos" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="129" pageNumber="130" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="andes">
<emphasis id="B91AEAB5FF7CFF17D5B7F83F0F3AF83D" box="[444,610,1940,1966]" italics="true" pageId="129" pageNumber="130">Tenedos andes</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFFF4B56FF7CFF17D666F83F0E37F83D" author="Jocque, R. &amp; Baert, L." box="[621,879,1940,1967]" pageId="129" pageNumber="130" pagination="67 - 173" refId="ref79332" refString="Jocque, R. &amp; Baert, L. (2002) A revision of the Neotropical spider genera Tenedos O. P. - Cambridge and Ishania Chamberlin (Araneae, Zodariidae). Bulletin de l'Institut Royal des Sciences Naturelles de Belgique, Entomologie, 72, 67 - 173." type="journal article" year="2002">Jocqué &amp; Baert, 2002</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, resemble those of 
<taxonomicName id="4C6E4D24FF7CFF17D05FF83E099DF83D" authority="Martínez &amp; Brescovit &amp; Quijano, 2022" authorityName="Martínez &amp; Brescovit &amp; Quijano" authorityYear="2022" box="[1108,1221,1940,1966]" class="Arachnida" family="Zodariidae" genus="Tenedos" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="129" pageNumber="130" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="medina" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis id="B91AEAB5FF7CFF17D05FF83E099DF83D" box="[1108,1221,1940,1966]" italics="true" pageId="129" pageNumber="130">T. medina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B91AEAB5FF7CFF17D0DBF83F084AF83D" bold="true" box="[1232,1298,1940,1966]" pageId="129" pageNumber="130">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A22957CEFF7CFF17D0DBF83F084AF83D" box="[1232,1298,1940,1966]" pageId="129" pageNumber="130" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C6E4D24FF7CFF17D144F83E0C5AF841" authority="Martínez &amp; Brescovit &amp; Quijano, 2022" authorityName="Martínez &amp; Brescovit &amp; Quijano" authorityYear="2022" class="Arachnida" family="Zodariidae" genus="Tenedos" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="129" pageNumber="130" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="carlosprietoi" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis id="B91AEAB5FF7CFF17D144F83E0C5AF841" italics="true" pageId="129" pageNumber="130">T. carlosprietoi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B91AEAB5FF7CFF17D501F8130C12F841" bold="true" box="[266,330,1976,2002]" pageId="129" pageNumber="130">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A22957CEFF7CFF17D501F8130C12F841" box="[266,330,1976,2002]" pageId="129" pageNumber="130" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, by the presence of basal retrolateral tibial apophysis (bRTA); rounded concave median apophysis (MA) (see 
<bibRefCitation id="EFFF4B56FF7CFF17D51AF8770F69F865" author="Jocque, R. &amp; Baert, L." box="[273,561,2012,2039]" pageId="129" pageNumber="130" pagination="67 - 173" refId="ref79332" refString="Jocque, R. &amp; Baert, L. (2002) A revision of the Neotropical spider genera Tenedos O. P. - Cambridge and Ishania Chamberlin (Araneae, Zodariidae). Bulletin de l'Institut Royal des Sciences Naturelles de Belgique, Entomologie, 72, 67 - 173." type="journal article" year="2002">Jocqué &amp; Baert, 2002: 83</bibRefCitation>
, fig. 7A–B; figs 94A–D; 95A–B; 97A–D, 98A–B; 99A–F; 101A–D; 102A–B; 104A–D), but can be distinguished by median apophysis with slight notch at external edge, long, wide; apically rounded retrolateral tibial apophysis (RTA); short and quadrangular basal retrolateral tibial apophysis close to retrolateral tibial apophysis (
<figureCitation id="13552A22FF7FFF14D5B7FF740F13FF6A" box="[444,587,223,249]" captionStart="FIGURE 94" captionStartId="132.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[250,1326,191,1920]" captionTargetId="figure-27@132.[250,1338,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="132" captionText="FIGURE 94. Tenedos andes Jocqué &amp; Baert, 2002. A–B. Male palp (AMNH_IZC 00217585): A. Prolateral view. B. Retroventral view. C. Ventral view. D. Retrolateral view. E–F. Female epigyne (ICN-Ar-8021): E. Ventral view. F. Dorsal view. Scale bars: A–B: 200µm; C–D: 500µm; E–F: 100µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6521016" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6521016/files/figure.png" pageId="130" pageNumber="131">Figs 94A–D</figureCitation>
; 
<figureCitation id="13552A22FF7FFF14D65DFF750FF3FF6A" box="[598,683,222,249]" captionStart="FIGURE 95" captionStartId="133.[151,250,1702,1726]" captionTargetBox="[151,1423,186,1674]" captionTargetId="figure-19@133.[151,1436,181,1678]" captionTargetPageId="133" captionText="FIGURE 95. Tenedos andes Jocqué &amp; Baert, 2002. A–B. Male palp (AMNH_IZC 00217585): A. Ventral view. B. Retrolateral view. C–D. Female epigyne (ICN-Ar-8021): C. Ventral view. D. Dorsal view. Scale bars: A–B: 200µm; C–D: 500µm. Abbreviations: A, atrium; ApC, appendix of the conductor; bRTA, basal retrolateral tibial apophysis; C, conductor; E, embolus; FD, fertilization ducts; LB, lateral borders; MA, median apophysis; MFP, median field plate; RPC, retrolateral process of the cymbium; RTA, retrolateral tibial apophysis; S, spermathecae; SD, spermatic ducts; SR, seminal receptacles; T, tegulum; VTA, ventral tibial apophysis." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6521020" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6521020/files/figure.png" pageId="130" pageNumber="131">95A–B</figureCitation>
). Females are similar to those of 
<taxonomicName id="4C6E4D24FF7FFF14D02BFF74098CFF6A" authority="Martínez &amp; Brescovit &amp; Quijano, 2022" authorityName="Martínez &amp; Brescovit &amp; Quijano" authorityYear="2022" box="[1056,1236,223,249]" class="Arachnida" family="Zodariidae" genus="Tenedos" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="130" pageNumber="131" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="medina" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis id="B91AEAB5FF7FFF14D02BFF74098CFF6A" box="[1056,1236,223,249]" italics="true" pageId="130" pageNumber="131">Tenedos medina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B91AEAB5FF7FFF14D0D7FF740844FF6A" bold="true" box="[1244,1308,223,249]" pageId="130" pageNumber="131">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A22957CEFF7FFF14D0D7FF740844FF6A" box="[1244,1308,223,249]" pageId="130" pageNumber="131" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C6E4D24FF7FFF14D159FF740C5AFE8E" authority="Martínez &amp; Brescovit &amp; Quijano, 2022" authorityName="Martínez &amp; Brescovit &amp; Quijano" authorityYear="2022" class="Arachnida" family="Zodariidae" genus="Tenedos" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="130" pageNumber="131" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="carlosprietoi" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis id="B91AEAB5FF7FFF14D159FF740C5AFE8E" italics="true" pageId="130" pageNumber="131">T. carlosprietoi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B91AEAB5FF7FFF14D502FEA80C1FFE8E" bold="true" box="[265,327,259,285]" pageId="130" pageNumber="131">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A22957CEFF7FFF14D502FEA80C1FFE8E" box="[265,327,259,285]" pageId="130" pageNumber="131" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, by curved lateral borders, forming large atrium (A) (
<figureCitation id="13552A22FF7FFF14D793FEA80946FE8E" box="[920,1054,259,285]" captionStart="FIGURE 94" captionStartId="132.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[250,1326,191,1920]" captionTargetId="figure-27@132.[250,1338,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="132" captionText="FIGURE 94. Tenedos andes Jocqué &amp; Baert, 2002. A–B. Male palp (AMNH_IZC 00217585): A. Prolateral view. B. Retroventral view. C. Ventral view. D. Retrolateral view. E–F. Female epigyne (ICN-Ar-8021): E. Ventral view. F. Dorsal view. Scale bars: A–B: 200µm; C–D: 500µm; E–F: 100µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6521016" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6521016/files/figure.png" pageId="130" pageNumber="131">Figs 94E–F</figureCitation>
; 
<figureCitation id="13552A22FF7FFF14D023FEA90925FE8E" box="[1064,1149,258,285]" captionStart="FIGURE 95" captionStartId="133.[151,250,1702,1726]" captionTargetBox="[151,1423,186,1674]" captionTargetId="figure-19@133.[151,1436,181,1678]" captionTargetPageId="133" captionText="FIGURE 95. Tenedos andes Jocqué &amp; Baert, 2002. A–B. Male palp (AMNH_IZC 00217585): A. Ventral view. B. Retrolateral view. C–D. Female epigyne (ICN-Ar-8021): C. Ventral view. D. Dorsal view. Scale bars: A–B: 200µm; C–D: 500µm. Abbreviations: A, atrium; ApC, appendix of the conductor; bRTA, basal retrolateral tibial apophysis; C, conductor; E, embolus; FD, fertilization ducts; LB, lateral borders; MA, median apophysis; MFP, median field plate; RPC, retrolateral process of the cymbium; RTA, retrolateral tibial apophysis; S, spermathecae; SD, spermatic ducts; SR, seminal receptacles; T, tegulum; VTA, ventral tibial apophysis." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6521020" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6521020/files/figure.png" pageId="130" pageNumber="131">95C–D</figureCitation>
; 
<figureCitation id="13552A22FF7FFF14D08CFEA8098BFE8E" box="[1159,1235,259,285]" captionStart="FIGURE 97" captionStartId="136.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[241,1335,181,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-27@136.[241,1347,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="136" captionText="FIGURE 97. Tenedos medina sp. n. A–B. Male palp (MPUJ_ENT 0061989): A. Prolateral view. B. Retroventral view. C. Ventral view. D. Retrolateral view. E–F. Female epigyne (MPUJ_ENT 0068177): E. Ventral view. F. Dorsal view. Scale bars: A–D: 500µm; E–F: 100µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6521024" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6521024/files/figure.png" pageId="130" pageNumber="131">97E–F</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="13552A22FF7FFF14D0D6FEA80869FE8E" box="[1245,1329,259,285]" captionStart="FIGURE 98" captionStartId="137.[151,250,1678,1702]" captionTargetBox="[154,1427,181,1647]" captionTargetId="figure-19@137.[151,1436,181,1654]" captionTargetPageId="137" captionText="FIGURE 98. Tenedos medina sp. n. A–B. Male palp (MPUJ_ENT 0061989): A. Ventral view. B. Retrolateral view. C–D. Female epigyne (MPUJ_ENT 0068177): C. Ventral view. D. Dorsal view. Scale bars: A–B: 200µm; C–D: 500µm. Abbreviations: A, atrium; ApC, appendix of the conductor; bRTA, basal retrolateral tibial apophysis; E, embolus; FD, fertilization ducts; LB, lateral borders; MA, median apophysis; MFP, median field plate; RTA, retrolateral tibial apophysis; SR, seminal receptacles; VTA, ventral tibial apophysis." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6521028" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6521028/files/figure.png" pageId="130" pageNumber="131">98C–D</figureCitation>
; 
<figureCitation id="13552A22FF7FFF14D137FEA808C0FE8E" box="[1340,1432,259,285]" captionStart="FIGURE 101" captionStartId="141.[151,250,1944,1968]" captionTargetBox="[295,1291,188,1921]" captionTargetId="figure-19@141.[295,1291,181,1921]" captionTargetPageId="141" captionText="FIGURE 101. Tenedos carlosprietoi sp. n. A–B. Male palp (IAvH-I-605): A. Prolateral view. B. Retroventral view. C. Ventral view. D. Retrolateral view. E–F. Female epigyne (IAvH-I-3007): E. Ventral view. F. Dorsal view. Scale bars:A–D: 500µm; E–F: 100µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6521038" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6521038/files/figure.png" pageId="130" pageNumber="131">101E–F</figureCitation>
; 
<figureCitation id="13552A22FF7FFF14D49CFE8C0DA2FED2" box="[151,250,295,321]" captionStart="FIGURE 102" captionStartId="142.[151,250,1679,1703]" captionTargetBox="[156,1436,188,1646]" captionTargetId="figure-27@142.[151,1436,181,1656]" captionTargetPageId="142" captionText="FIGURE 102. Tenedos carlosprietoi sp. n. A–B. Male palp (IAvH-I-605): A. Ventral view. B. Retrolateral view. C–D. Female epigyne (IAvH-I-3007): C. Ventral view. D. Dorsal view. Abbreviations: A, atrium; bRTA, basal retrolateral tibial apophysis; E, embolus; FD, fertilization ducts; LB, lateral borders; MA, median apophysis; MFP, median field plate; RTA, retrolateral tibial apophysis; S, spermathecae; SR, seminal receptacles." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6521040" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6521040/files/figure.png" pageId="130" pageNumber="131">102C–D</figureCitation>
; 
<figureCitation id="13552A22FF7FFF14D50EFE8C0C3AFED2" box="[261,354,295,321]" captionStart="FIGURE 104" captionStartId="144.[151,250,1944,1968]" captionTargetBox="[266,1321,195,1921]" captionTargetId="figure-27@144.[266,1321,181,1921]" captionTargetPageId="144" captionText="FIGURE 104. Tenedos carlosprietoi sp. n. A–B. Male palp (IAvH-I-606): A. Prolateral view. B. Retroventral view. C. Ventral view. D. Retrolateral view. E–F. Female epigyne (IAvH-I-614): E. Ventral view. F. Dorsal view. Scale bars:A–D: 500µm; E–F: 100µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6521044" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6521044/files/figure.png" pageId="130" pageNumber="131">104E–F</figureCitation>
), but can be recognized by very large median field plate (MFP), occupying almost 50% of dorsal region of epigyne, short lateral borders (LB) thin at basal side; long and thin seminal receptacles (SR) (
<figureCitation id="13552A22FF7FFF14D119FEE008C0FEF6" box="[1298,1432,331,357]" captionStart="FIGURE 94" captionStartId="132.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[250,1326,191,1920]" captionTargetId="figure-27@132.[250,1338,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="132" captionText="FIGURE 94. Tenedos andes Jocqué &amp; Baert, 2002. A–B. Male palp (AMNH_IZC 00217585): A. Prolateral view. B. Retroventral view. C. Ventral view. D. Retrolateral view. E–F. Female epigyne (ICN-Ar-8021): E. Ventral view. F. Dorsal view. Scale bars: A–B: 200µm; C–D: 500µm; E–F: 100µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6521016" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6521016/files/figure.png" pageId="130" pageNumber="131">Figs 94E–F</figureCitation>
; 
<figureCitation id="13552A22FF7FFF14D49CFEC50DB4FE1A" box="[151,236,366,393]" captionStart="FIGURE 95" captionStartId="133.[151,250,1702,1726]" captionTargetBox="[151,1423,186,1674]" captionTargetId="figure-19@133.[151,1436,181,1678]" captionTargetPageId="133" captionText="FIGURE 95. Tenedos andes Jocqué &amp; Baert, 2002. A–B. Male palp (AMNH_IZC 00217585): A. Ventral view. B. Retrolateral view. C–D. Female epigyne (ICN-Ar-8021): C. Ventral view. D. Dorsal view. Scale bars: A–B: 200µm; C–D: 500µm. Abbreviations: A, atrium; ApC, appendix of the conductor; bRTA, basal retrolateral tibial apophysis; C, conductor; E, embolus; FD, fertilization ducts; LB, lateral borders; MA, median apophysis; MFP, median field plate; RPC, retrolateral process of the cymbium; RTA, retrolateral tibial apophysis; S, spermathecae; SD, spermatic ducts; SR, seminal receptacles; T, tegulum; VTA, ventral tibial apophysis." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6521020" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6521020/files/figure.png" pageId="130" pageNumber="131">95C–D</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C374652CFF7FFF14D4CCFE3909C4F896" pageId="130" pageNumber="131" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BD136A7FF7FFF14D4CCFE390EC3FA9E" blockId="130.[151,1437,151,1834]" pageId="130" pageNumber="131">
<emphasis id="B91AEAB5FF7FFF14D4CCFE390C2DFE3F" bold="true" box="[199,373,402,428]" pageId="130" pageNumber="131">Redescription.</emphasis>
<emphasis id="B91AEAB5FF7FFF14D576FE380CEFFE3E" box="[381,439,403,429]" italics="true" pageId="130" pageNumber="131">Male</emphasis>
(
<typeStatus id="54D58805FF7FFF14D5CDFE380F6BFE3E" box="[454,563,403,429]" pageId="130" pageNumber="131">Holotype</typeStatus>
, AMNH_IZC 00217585). 
<materialsCitation id="3B063CFAFF7FFF14D754FE380ECFFA9E" collectionCode="II, III, RPC, T, EB, BTM, VTA, RTA" collectorName="Coloration &amp; Chelicerae &amp; Endites &amp; Labium &amp; Legs &amp; Coxae I &amp; Femora I &amp; Patella I &amp; Tibia I &amp; Metatarsus I &amp; Tarsi I" pageId="130" pageNumber="131" specimenCount="1">
<collectorName id="269B5371FF7FFF14D754FE380E8FFE3E" box="[863,983,403,429]" pageId="130" pageNumber="131">Coloration</collectorName>
(
<figureCitation id="13552A22FF7FFF14D7E3FE38092CFE3E" box="[1000,1140,403,429]" captionStart="FIGURE 93" captionStartId="131.[151,250,1912,1936]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,181,1865]" captionTargetId="figure-19@131.[151,1436,181,1889]" captionTargetPageId="131" captionText="FIGURE 93. Tenedos andes Jocqué &amp; Baert, 2002. A–B. Male habitus (AMNH_IZC 00217585): A. Dorsal view. B. Ventral view. C–D. Female habitus (ICN-Ar-8021): C. Dorsal view. D. Ventral view. Scale bar: A–D: 2mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6521014" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6521014/files/figure.png" pageId="130" pageNumber="131">Fig. 93A–B</figureCitation>
): carapace brown-reddish. 
<collectorName id="269B5371FF7FFF14D49CFE1C0C57FE42" box="[151,271,439,465]" pageId="130" pageNumber="131">Chelicerae</collectorName>
with paturon brown, fangs brown-reddish. 
<collectorName id="269B5371FF7FFF14D70AFE1C0E0DFE42" box="[769,853,439,465]" pageId="130" pageNumber="131">Endites</collectorName>
light brown, white on anterior region. 
<collectorName id="269B5371FF7FFF14D11FFE1C0833FE42" box="[1300,1387,439,465]" pageId="130" pageNumber="131">Labium</collectorName>
and sternum light brown. 
<collectorName id="269B5371FF7FFF14D586FE700C90FE66" box="[397,456,475,501]" pageId="130" pageNumber="131">Legs</collectorName>
: 
<collectorName id="269B5371FF7FFF14D5DFFE700F75FE66" box="[468,557,475,501]" pageId="130" pageNumber="131">Coxae I</collectorName>
–IV pale beige. 
<collectorName id="269B5371FF7FFF14D6EEFE700E14FE66" box="[741,844,475,501]" pageId="130" pageNumber="131">Femora I</collectorName>
–IV light yellow from base to medial region, brown the rest of their extension. 
<collectorName id="269B5371FF7FFF14D5B4FE540F43FD8A" box="[447,539,511,537]" pageId="130" pageNumber="131">Patella I</collectorName>
yellow, 
<collectionCode id="ED7FAE62FF7FFF14D672FE540FD3FD8A" box="[633,651,511,537]" pageId="130" pageNumber="131">II</collectionCode>
–IV light brown. 
<collectorName id="269B5371FF7FFF14D747FE540ECDFD8A" box="[844,917,511,537]" pageId="130" pageNumber="131">Tibia I</collectorName>
pale yellow with dark spots on the base, 
<collectionCode id="ED7FAE62FF7FFF14D155FE540828FD8A" box="[1374,1392,511,537]" pageId="130" pageNumber="131">II</collectionCode>
–IV yellow with dark lateral spots. 
<collectorName id="269B5371FF7FFF14D5F1FD880FDFFDAE" box="[506,647,547,573]" pageId="130" pageNumber="131">Metatarsus I</collectorName>
brown, 
<collectionCode id="ED7FAE62FF7FFF14D6E3FD880FA2FDAE" box="[744,762,547,573]" pageId="130" pageNumber="131">II</collectionCode>
–IV yellow with dark spots on the base. 
<collectorName id="269B5371FF7FFF14D0C6FD88084FFDAE" box="[1229,1303,547,573]" pageId="130" pageNumber="131">Tarsi I</collectorName>
–IV yellow. Abdomen: dorsally dark gray with ten white guanine spots organized as follows: two irregular spots very close to each other partially fused in medial region, anteriorly positioned; two longitudinal spots larger than previous ones, anteromedially positioned; four irregular spots, forming a cross, medially positioned; two large and irregular spots, posteriorly positioned. Laterally dark gray with a wide and oblique longitudinal stripe, extending to posterior side. Ventrally light gray with two large anterior spots and several small light spots uniformly distributed on abdomen. Spinnerets light yellow. Measurements: total length 5.61, carapace length 2.82, width 1.84, height 1.21. Clypeus height 0.55. Eye diameters and interdistances: AME 0.09, ALE 0.10, PME 0.09, PLE 0.11; AME–AME 0.22, AME–ALE 0.23, AME–PME 0.21, PME–PME 0.24, PME–PLE 0.37, ALE–PLE 0.23. Chelicerae 0.90 length. Sternum length 1.12, width 0.97. Legs: I—femur 1.64/ patella 0.64/ tibia 1.70/ metatarsus 1.41/ tarsus 0.92/ total 6.31; 
<collectionCode id="ED7FAE62FF7FFF14D4DDFC200DB0FC36" box="[214,232,907,933]" pageId="130" pageNumber="131">II</collectionCode>
—1.36/ 0.64/ 1.25/ 1.28/ 0.81/ 5.34; 
<collectionCode id="ED7FAE62FF7FFF14D675FC210FC2FC36" box="[638,666,906,933]" pageId="130" pageNumber="131">III</collectionCode>
—1.45/ 0.45/ 1.25/ 1.58/ 0.78/ 5.51; IV—2.01/ 0.63/ 1.48/ 2.12/ 1.14/ 7.38. Abdomen length 2.61. Legs spines pattern (only the differences from the general pattern): 
<collectionCode id="ED7FAE62FF7FFF14D0C2FC040983FC5A" box="[1225,1243,943,969]" pageId="130" pageNumber="131">II</collectionCode>
—metatarsus p0- 1d-1; 
<collectionCode id="ED7FAE62FF7FFF14D4D2FC780DACFC7E" box="[217,244,979,1005]" pageId="130" pageNumber="131">III</collectionCode>
—femur d0-0-1, metatarsus p1d-1-2; IV—metatarsus d1-1-0. Palp: retrolateral process of cymbium (
<collectionCode id="ED7FAE62FF7FFF14D157FC7808CCFC7E" box="[1372,1428,979,1005]" pageId="130" pageNumber="131">RPC</collectionCode>
) long, wide with small rounded projection on anterior side; tegulum (
<collectionCode id="ED7FAE62FF7FFF14D79AFC5C0EFCFB82" box="[913,932,1015,1041]" name="Tavera, Department of Geology and Geophysics" pageId="130" pageNumber="131">T</collectionCode>
) large, rounded, almost as long as wide; subtegulum (St) large, longer than wide; conductor (C) developed, wide with granulate cuticle; appendix (ApC) short, apically sharp; embolus (E) long, filiform towards apex; base of embolus (
<collectionCode id="ED7FAE62FF7FFF14D7DAFB940EAFFBCA" box="[977,1015,1087,1113]" pageId="130" pageNumber="131">EB</collectionCode>
) approximately as long as three times as basal tegular membrane width; basal tegular membrane (
<collectionCode id="ED7FAE62FF7FFF14D74AFBC80ED9FBEE" box="[833,897,1123,1149]" pageId="130" pageNumber="131">BTM</collectionCode>
) originated proximally on tegulum, proximally flattened, ending as short, sharp appendix; spermatic ducts (SD) S-shaped, both folds full open, thin; ventral tibial apophysis (
<collectionCode id="ED7FAE62FF7FFF14D51DFB000C09FB56" box="[278,337,1195,1221]" country="France" name="Jardin Botanique de la Villa Thuret" pageId="130" pageNumber="131" type="Herbarium">VTA</collectionCode>
) small, triangular-shaped in ventral view; median apophysis (MA) large, rounded, slight notch on external edge; retrolateral tibial apophysis (
<collectionCode id="ED7FAE62FF7FFF14D68DFB640FE6FB7A" box="[646,702,1231,1257]" pageId="130" pageNumber="131">RTA</collectionCode>
) large, longer than palpal tibia, shovel-shaped; basal retrolateral tibial apophysis (bRTA) short, square-shaped (
<figureCitation id="13552A22FF7FFF14D694FB580E77FA9E" box="[671,815,1267,1293]" captionStart="FIGURE 94" captionStartId="132.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[250,1326,191,1920]" captionTargetId="figure-27@132.[250,1338,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="132" captionText="FIGURE 94. Tenedos andes Jocqué &amp; Baert, 2002. A–B. Male palp (AMNH_IZC 00217585): A. Prolateral view. B. Retroventral view. C. Ventral view. D. Retrolateral view. E–F. Female epigyne (ICN-Ar-8021): E. Ventral view. F. Dorsal view. Scale bars: A–B: 200µm; C–D: 500µm; E–F: 100µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6521016" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6521016/files/figure.png" pageId="130" pageNumber="131">Figs 94A–D</figureCitation>
; 
<figureCitation id="13552A22FF7FFF14D732FB590ED6FA9E" box="[825,910,1266,1293]" captionStart="FIGURE 95" captionStartId="133.[151,250,1702,1726]" captionTargetBox="[151,1423,186,1674]" captionTargetId="figure-19@133.[151,1436,181,1678]" captionTargetPageId="133" captionText="FIGURE 95. Tenedos andes Jocqué &amp; Baert, 2002. A–B. Male palp (AMNH_IZC 00217585): A. Ventral view. B. Retrolateral view. C–D. Female epigyne (ICN-Ar-8021): C. Ventral view. D. Dorsal view. Scale bars: A–B: 200µm; C–D: 500µm. Abbreviations: A, atrium; ApC, appendix of the conductor; bRTA, basal retrolateral tibial apophysis; C, conductor; E, embolus; FD, fertilization ducts; LB, lateral borders; MA, median apophysis; MFP, median field plate; RPC, retrolateral process of the cymbium; RTA, retrolateral tibial apophysis; S, spermathecae; SD, spermatic ducts; SR, seminal receptacles; T, tegulum; VTA, ventral tibial apophysis." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6521020" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6521020/files/figure.png" pageId="130" pageNumber="131">95A–B</figureCitation>
)
</materialsCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD136A7FF7FFF14D4CCFABC0DA1F92E" blockId="130.[151,1437,151,1834]" pageId="130" pageNumber="131">
<emphasis id="B91AEAB5FF7FFF14D4CCFABC0C43FAA2" box="[199,283,1303,1329]" italics="true" pageId="130" pageNumber="131">Female</emphasis>
(ICN-Ar-8021). Coloration and abdominal pattern of spots as male (
<figureCitation id="13552A22FF7FFF14D017FABC09FEFAA2" box="[1052,1190,1303,1329]" captionStart="FIGURE 93" captionStartId="131.[151,250,1912,1936]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,181,1865]" captionTargetId="figure-19@131.[151,1436,181,1889]" captionTargetPageId="131" captionText="FIGURE 93. Tenedos andes Jocqué &amp; Baert, 2002. A–B. Male habitus (AMNH_IZC 00217585): A. Dorsal view. B. Ventral view. C–D. Female habitus (ICN-Ar-8021): C. Dorsal view. D. Ventral view. Scale bar: A–D: 2mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6521014" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6521014/files/figure.png" pageId="130" pageNumber="131">Fig. 93C–D</figureCitation>
). Measurements: total length 7.23, carapace length 3.71, width 2.47, height 1.59. Clypeus height 0.71. Eye diameters and interdistances: AME 0.10, ALE 0.11, PME 0.13, PLE 0.14; AME–AME 0.24, AME–ALE 0.32, AME–PME 0.36, PME–PME 0.32, PME–PLE 0.51, ALE–PLE 0.35. Chelicerae 1.51 length. Sternum length 1.31, width 1.30. Legs: I—femur 2.18/ patella 0.73/ tibia 1.78/ metatarsus 1.49/ tarsus 1.14/ total 7.32; II—1.85/ 0.63/ 1.48/ 1.41/ 0.92/ 6.29; III—1.71/ 0.62/ 1.25/ 1.66/ 0.94/ 6.18; IV—2.02/ 0.85/ 1.67/ 2.51/ 1.18/ 8.23. Abdomen length 3.72. Legs spines pattern (only the differences from the general pattern): IV—femur d0-0-1d, tibia v1p-1p-2, metatarsus d1p-1p-0. Epigyne: lateral borders (LB) short, curved towards posteromedial region of epigyne, forming medial large atrium (A); median field plate (MFP) very large and quadrangular-shaped; copulatory ducts (CD) very short and wide, almost undistinguished from spermathecae; seminal receptacles (SR) long, thin, curved towards median septum; spermathecae (S) large, irregulars, posteriorly positioned; fertilization ducts (FD) almost as long as spermathecae length (
<figureCitation id="13552A22FF7FFF14D119F9D408C0F90A" box="[1298,1432,1663,1689]" captionStart="FIGURE 94" captionStartId="132.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[250,1326,191,1920]" captionTargetId="figure-27@132.[250,1338,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="132" captionText="FIGURE 94. Tenedos andes Jocqué &amp; Baert, 2002. A–B. Male palp (AMNH_IZC 00217585): A. Prolateral view. B. Retroventral view. C. Ventral view. D. Retrolateral view. E–F. Female epigyne (ICN-Ar-8021): E. Ventral view. F. Dorsal view. Scale bars: A–B: 200µm; C–D: 500µm; E–F: 100µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6521016" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6521016/files/figure.png" pageId="130" pageNumber="131">Figs 94E–F</figureCitation>
; 
<figureCitation id="13552A22FF7FFF14D49CF9090DB4F92E" box="[151,236,1698,1725]" captionStart="FIGURE 95" captionStartId="133.[151,250,1702,1726]" captionTargetBox="[151,1423,186,1674]" captionTargetId="figure-19@133.[151,1436,181,1678]" captionTargetPageId="133" captionText="FIGURE 95. Tenedos andes Jocqué &amp; Baert, 2002. A–B. Male palp (AMNH_IZC 00217585): A. Ventral view. B. Retrolateral view. C–D. Female epigyne (ICN-Ar-8021): C. Ventral view. D. Dorsal view. Scale bars: A–B: 200µm; C–D: 500µm. Abbreviations: A, atrium; ApC, appendix of the conductor; bRTA, basal retrolateral tibial apophysis; C, conductor; E, embolus; FD, fertilization ducts; LB, lateral borders; MA, median apophysis; MFP, median field plate; RPC, retrolateral process of the cymbium; RTA, retrolateral tibial apophysis; S, spermathecae; SD, spermatic ducts; SR, seminal receptacles; T, tegulum; VTA, ventral tibial apophysis." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6521020" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6521020/files/figure.png" pageId="130" pageNumber="131">95C–D</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD136A7FF7FFF14D4CCF96D09C4F896" blockId="130.[151,1437,151,1834]" pageId="130" pageNumber="131">
<emphasis id="B91AEAB5FF7FFF14D4CCF96D0C67F973" bold="true" box="[199,319,1734,1760]" pageId="130" pageNumber="131">Variation.</emphasis>
Males (n=4): total length: 5.61–6.11; carapace length: 2.82–2.99; femur I length: 2.11–2.23. Females (n=2): total length: 6.99–7.23; carapace length: 2.91–3.71; femur I length: 2.18–2.31.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
